The Police in Kebbi State, on Monday, said 16 persons, not 50, were killed by bandits in Dankade village on Friday. A number of armed men attacked the community in Danko/Wsaagu Local Government Area of the state. Public Relations Officer, DSP Nafi’u Abubakar told News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) the deceased include security operatives. He said the incident happened around 3.00pm as bandits coming from Zamfara invaded the Dankade and killed 13 civilians, 1 police officer and 2 soldiers. “Police patrol teams mobilised to the village and engaged them, resulting in the loss of one of our police officers and two army personnel. “Thirteen civilians were killed. We eliminated unknown number of bandits in the duel”, the PRO noted. The spokesman further confirmed that the criminals set some houses ablaze. Abubakar said investigation had commenced and urged the people to assist with information about the perpetrators.